rComments: He is definitely knowledgeable and is there if you need help. However, I felt that I learned more from the TA than him. We spoke Spanish for 15 mins each class in breakout rooms. I think the course would've been better in person or as a discussion group. There were many things to be graded on (homework, tests, quizzes, culminating tasks).
Awesome prof. He is engaging, a great lecturer, clear about expectations. You can tell he really cares about his students' success.
Really cool prof. I would take spanish with with him again! I loved his class!
He's really enthusiastic and loves the material. His class is fairly easy and as a native speaker he knows the language very well. No cons really, really cool professor, but attendance is mandatory.

The course itself is pretty easy, however I barely got the chance to speak spanish. The way he conducts the class isn't very good for conversation and we mostly did exercises from the books. I feel like this class didn't really advance my knowledge of spanish at all...

very nice as a person and clearlyknows the language. however, his lecture are very disorganized (and the blackboard). I love the language but don't expect to use it a whole lot in this class. A lot of textbook work with out real world examples of the language being used. A discussion group would work a lot better for this level of Spanish.
